---
title: Cheesy Taco Turkey & Bean Soup 2x the delicious servings!
description: Who doesn’t love a warming, cozy pot of soup? Break out your big spoons (and an extra leaf for the table) for this delicious one-pot, big batch, 30-minute dinner to warm up the whole crew. This one boasts all the flavors of savory turkey and bean tacos in one light, satisfying bowl. It starts with ground turkey sautéed with our blend of Southwest spices, plus garlic, onion, and tomato for a deeply flavored broth. You’ll add hearty red beans, shredded Mexican cheese, a dash of hot sauce, and finish with a sprinkle of fresh scallions (and even more cheese!).

This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65a55edf4bb81dc143a6ce0e-da2ac450.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65a55edf4bb81dc143a6ce0e.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-taco-turkey-and-bean-soup-65a55edf4bb81dc143a6ce0e
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 560 kcal
  fat: 28 g
  saturated fat: 10 g
  carbohydrates: 33 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1070 mg
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{4}, separating whites from greens. Dice @tomato{2}(diced).

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large heavy-bottomed pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{20%ounce}, @Southwest spice blend{2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until turkey is lightly browned and mostly cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Add garlic, scallion whites, and @tomato paste{2%unit}; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add diced tomatoes, @chicken stock concentrate{4%unit}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1.5%teaspoon} to pot with turkey mixture; stir until well combined.

> Use 3 tsp sugar for 8 servings.

Stir in @kidney beans{1%unit} and their liquid and @water{3%cups}; bring to a simmer and cook until tomatoes are softened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> Use 6 cups water for 8 servings.

Stir in half the @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup} and as much @hot sauce{2%teaspoon} as you like; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide soup between #bowls{}; top with scallion greens and remaining Mexican cheese blend. Serve.